Funny game but buggy. Buggy camera controls. Dodgy geometry issues and 
weird lines on some areas where geometry meets (I. E hills), no sense of 
direction when starting, the last page open in the menu (I. E map) isn't 
saved, so you keep having to press twice for the map or any other menu. The 
map is super basic. And most worrying of all, the last patch was well over 
a year ago - that last point made me get a refund. Other annoyances include 
a tab specifically for advertising your other sims and a very (purposely?) 
awkwardly placed share button a few notches down from the top right corner. 
I don't like that. The also don't like the walking animation, while it 
looks okay, it doesn't match with the speed of movement causing a sliding 
effect. Refunded.

A-MA-ZING. I am a HUGE Gluten Free Games fan, and their newest app, this one, is no exception. The graphics are great, the cats are very well rendered, (as usual), and the fact that you can have the lifestyle of a house cat, wild cat, street cat, mine cat, nature cat, or sewer cat, is on point. I even have 5 different cat families just so I can play all the different lifestyles! :D All the different coat colors keep me constantly thinking about which six coats I should choose for my cats! It has endless gameplay and the cat riding and driving the car and the skateboard cracks me up every time. XD Sure the cats make raccoon noises, the cars fly, and the people walk sideways. Just pretend its Harry Potter! XD All in all a must have for any simulator lover, even for the small price. ;)
